00:34:37,096 --> 00:34:39,993
to her conduct without
a more definitive causal link.

733
00:34:39,993 --> 00:34:43,601
You remember how Skoda said
Jamie has this need for attention?

734
00:34:43,601 --> 00:34:45,167
Well, I gave her my pager number

735
00:34:45,167 --> 00:34:46,984
in case she needed somebody to talk to...

736
00:34:46,984 --> 00:34:48,740
and guess who's been paging me?

737
00:34:48,740 --> 00:34:50,273
She's feeling needy.

738
00:34:50,273 --> 00:34:53,005
If Skoda's right,
it's more than need.

739
00:34:53,005 --> 00:34:55,432
I think she's jonesing for a sympathy fix.

740
00:34:55,432 --> 00:34:57,507
And what do you propose?

741
00:34:57,507 --> 00:34:59,221
Feed the junkie.

742
00:35:02,884 --> 00:35:04,901
Thanks for coming down.

743
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:10,406
I just want to help in whatever way I can.

744
00:35:10,406 --> 00:35:13,490
As you know, we're holding Justin
until he can be arraigned...

745
00:35:13,490 --> 00:35:17,123
and then we'll release him
into your custody...

746
00:35:17,655 --> 00:35:20,022
assuming you want to take him.

747
00:35:20,214 --> 00:35:21,982
I don't know.

748
00:35:21,982 --> 00:35:26,193
He scares me. I'm sure he just hurt
Emily to get back at me.

749
00:35:26,193 --> 00:35:29,756
Must be hard to be an outcast
in your own house.

750
00:35:29,756 --> 00:35:31,295
You don't know the half of it.

751
00:35:31,295 --> 00:35:32,993
Actually, I do.

752
00:35:40,865 --> 00:35:43,354
This is my file.

753
00:35:44,278 --> 00:35:46,393
I thought it was sealed.

754
00:35:46,393 --> 00:35:49,324
I have a friend in Children's Services.

755
00:35:49,324 --> 00:35:50,786
She remembered you.

756
00:35:50,786 --> 00:35:52,503
How?

757
00:35:53,189 --> 00:35:57,418
She remembered how nervous her superiors
were about investigating an ambassador

758
00:35:57,418 --> 00:36:01,617
for sexually abusing his
11-year-old daughter.

759
00:36:01,617 --> 00:36:04,781
It must have been
a very painful time for you.

760
00:36:05,212 --> 00:36:07,245
Yes, it was.

761
00:36:07,245 --> 00:36:09,528
How did your mother take it?

762
00:36:11,171 --> 00:36:15,430
She was jealous, because
Daddy couldn't stand to touch her.

763
00:36:15,718 --> 00:36:20,180
So she sent me away to boarding school.
I begged her not to but

764
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:24,503
what Mother wants, Mother gets.

765
00:36:24,503 --> 00:36:27,108
She abandoned you, Jamie.

766
00:36:28,221 --> 00:36:29,737
I survived.

767
00:36:29,737 --> 00:36:34,564
But still. Must be hard facing that kind
of rejection from your own daughter.

768
00:36:34,564 --> 00:36:36,904
What do you mean?

769
00:36:37,056 --> 00:36:40,279
Emily came out of her coma
a few hours ago.

770
00:36:40,279 --> 00:36:43,035
She told us everything.

771
00:36:43,035 --> 00:36:45,591
She wants to see you.

772
00:36:46,509 --> 00:36:51,675
But first you and I have a couple of details
we need to straighten out.

773
00:36:53,168 --> 00:36:55,432
What details?

774
00:36:56,049 --> 00:36:59,548
- Let's start with the hairbrush.
- It's Justin's.

775
00:36:59,548 --> 00:37:02,443
Yes, but we got a partial print...

776
00:37:02,443 --> 00:37:05,942
- and with Emily's testimony...
- Emily's a liar.

777
00:37:06,684 --> 00:37:11,778
- Now why would she lie?
- Her father poisoned her against me.

778
00:37:12,547 --> 00:37:17,463
It's been very painful, very hurtful.

779
00:37:19,186 --> 00:37:21,124
I know, Jamie.

780
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:24,712
Been carrying the pain long enough.

781
00:37:25,059 --> 00:37:27,981
Just tell me your side of the story

782
00:37:27,981 --> 00:37:30,955
and you can start to heal.

783
00:37:37,990 --> 00:37:42,673
We were driving home and
she wouldn't stop crying

784
00:37:43,265 --> 00:37:48,416
so I pulled over to try and talk to her.

785
00:37:48,683 --> 00:37:54,248
But when she told me she and her daddy
were leaving me forever...

786
00:37:54,916 --> 00:37:58,666
I pulled her out of the car and
she hit her head on the curb.

787
00:37:58,666 --> 00:38:01,262
- How?
- She fell.

788
00:38:01,262 --> 00:38:02,957
Come on, Jamie.

789
00:38:07,043 --> 00:38:09,821
I didn't shove her hard.

790
00:38:09,821 --> 00:38:12,427
I just wanted her to stop whining...

791
00:38:12,427 --> 00:38:14,059
so I could talk to her.

792
00:38:14,059 --> 00:38:16,400
Did that stop her?

793
00:38:16,900 --> 00:38:21,159
It was the first time
she was quiet all day.

794
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:24,277
And she was sleepy.

795
00:38:24,277 --> 00:38:29,923
So when I got home, I put her to bed and
Michael and I went to the drugstore.

796
00:38:31,020 --> 00:38:34,274
But when we came back...

797
00:38:34,274 --> 00:38:37,864
she was crying again.

798
00:38:38,027 --> 00:38:39,697
I told her...

799
00:38:39,697 --> 00:38:43,664
how important it was for her
to be a good girl...

800
00:38:43,664 --> 00:38:48,099
so that her new daddy could love her,
too, but she wouldn't stop.

801
00:38:48,730 --> 00:38:52,135
It was like she was doing it to spite me.

802
00:38:52,135 --> 00:38:53,935
Is that why you used the hairbrush?

803
00:38:53,935 --> 00:38:55,592
I had to teach her discipline.

804
00:38:55,592 --> 00:38:58,040
My mother used a hairbrush to teach me

805
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:03,458
but Emily just kept screaming louder and
louder, what was I supposed to do?

806
00:39:03,664 --> 00:39:06,395
The only thing you could do.

807
00:39:11,393 --> 00:39:15,110
I threw her against the wall.

808
00:39:15,361 --> 00:39:17,716
Then what?

809
00:39:19,989 --> 00:39:24,413
She finally stopped.

810
00:39:28,950 --> 00:39:32,245
And then I tucked her into bed
kissed her on her cheek,

811
00:39:32,245 --> 00:39:36,170
and then I told her I loved her.

812
00:39:40,041 --> 00:39:43,915
I just wanted her to stop crying.

813
00:39:45,915 --> 00:39:49,147
Was that too much to ask?

814
00:40:11,891 --> 00:40:13,689
It's good work, John.

815
00:40:32,627 --> 00:40:37,193
Took a chance with that bluff about Emily
coming out of her coma.

816
00:40:37,411 --> 00:40:42,034
I'm not sure what we would have done
if Jamie had pressed to see her.

817
00:40:44,833 --> 00:40:47,595
She didn't care about the kids.

818
00:40:49,219 --> 00:40:51,232
How did you know?

819
00:40:52,239 --> 00:40:53,969
We searched her house...

820
00:40:53,969 --> 00:40:56,821
I looked at that four-year-old...

821
00:40:57,013 --> 00:40:59,800
flashed on a little girl that used to live
across the street from us

822
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:03,183
in our old neighborhood
on the Lower East Side.

823
00:41:03,183 --> 00:41:06,167
She had that same look in her eyes.

824
00:41:06,540 --> 00:41:08,280
What look?

825
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:11,468
Sad, lost.

826
00:41:14,219 --> 00:41:19,289
She used to stand on her porch every
afternoon when I came home from school.

827
00:41:19,289 --> 00:41:21,805
Like she was waiting for me.

828
00:41:21,805 --> 00:41:27,326
Sometimes, she'd have
a black eye or a bloody lip.

829
00:41:29,029 --> 00:41:30,577
Never said anything to me.

830
00:41:30,577 --> 00:41:33,949
Just looked at me like
she was trying to tell me something.

831
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:38,825
But I was too full of my own teenage crap
to pay any attention.

832
00:41:39,308 --> 00:41:42,346
One day, I came home...

833
00:41:43,067 --> 00:41:45,560
she wasn't there.

834
00:41:47,349 --> 00:41:52,050
Found out her mother threw her through
a plate glass window.

835
00:41:53,994 --> 00:41:56,822
Went to the funeral.

836
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:59,922
Saw her dad.

837
00:42:00,866 --> 00:42:04,897
It's the first time I saw a grown man cry.

838
00:42:05,950 --> 00:42:09,037
What happened to her mother?

839
00:42:09,037 --> 00:42:12,004
They sent her to a sanitarium.

840
00:42:12,004 --> 00:42:13,544
She told my mother...

841
00:42:13,544 --> 00:42:16,024
